OL,3,CWhat is the difference between the
OL,4,Cpension triple lock and triple lock
OL,5,Cplus?
OL,7,FWhat is personal allowance?
OL,9,FPersonal allowance is the amount of
OL,10,Fmoney you can earn or receive in a
OL,11,Fyear without having to pay any tax.
OL,13,FThe standard personal allowance is
OL,14,F#12,570. It depends on your age, and
OL,15,Fhow much you earn.
OL,17,FYou pay tax on your pension if your
OL,18,Ftotal annual income is bigger than
OL,19,Fyour personal allowance.
